headlines.description: Kentavious Caldwell-Pope scored 21 points to lead all five Detroit starters in double figures, carrying the Pistons to a surprising 106-94 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons surprise Hawks on opening night, winning 106-94

headlines.description: Pau Gasol blocked a potential tying layup by LeBron James, and Jimmy Butler then broke up a last-second inbounds pass intended for James as the Bulls beat the Cavs 97-95 in their season opener.

video.headline: Bulls fend off Cavs to start season

headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls turn back Cavs on Gasol's block of LeBron

headlines.description: Reigning NBA MVP Stephen Curry showed he hasn't lost a step or his swagger by scoring 40 points to lead the Golden State Warriors to a 111-95 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Tuesday.

video.headline: Curry scores 40 as Warriors open title defense with win

headlines.shortLinkText: Curry puts up 40 as Warriors win on banner night
